One of the special features of DSSCs is their photoanodes. Unlike other kinds of solar cells, including silicon- based solar cells, thin-film solar cells, and organic solar cells, DSSCs have thick light-absorbing electrodes, i.e., photoanodes, of 10~20 μm, almost 100 times thicker than other solar cells. Therefore, the generation of electrons in the dye and diffusion and recombination of electrons through the electrode occur simultaneously according to the continuity equation15:1-∇⋅(D∇n)-k(n-n0)=λI(x)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
